  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your rigatoni on to boil in a large pan of salted water. Cook until al dente."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Set a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Dice your aubergine into roughly 2cm squares. Roughly chop your mint."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your aubergines to the pan with a good pinch of salt and keep them moving. Fry for about 3 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the aubergine has taken on some colour, add the ‘nduja and a splash of the pasta cooking water. Mix well."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now, add the oregano and a good drizzle of olive oil, mix again and cook for another couple of mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finally, drain your pasta (reserving a little pasta water) and add to the pan with the aubergine. Keep mixing over a medium heat until you have a thick glossy sauce, adding splashes of pasta water where necessary."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finally, add a handful of mint and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Plate up and top with grated pecorino, if you like. Serve and enjoy."
    }
  ],
